<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="K" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Knighthood" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Knighthood,</orth> 1) chivalry: <cit><quote>O shame to k.</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 197" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 197</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>conjures him by k., gentry,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 197" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 197</bibl></cit> <bibl n="shak. luc 197" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 197</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r2 1.1.75" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 1, 75</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 5.3.145" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. V, 3, 145</bibl>.<lb />2) the rank and dignity of a knight: <cit><quote>laid my k. on my shoulder,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 1.1.79" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 1, 79</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.14" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.2.58" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 2, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.2.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 2, 6</bibl>.
<lb />3) the being one of an order of chivalry: <cit><quote>buckled below fair --'s bending knee,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.5.76" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. V, 5, 76</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>this ornament of k.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.1.29" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 1, 29</bibl></cit>.
<lb />4) rank of a baronet: <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.3.137" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 3, 137</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.2.93" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 2, 93</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.3.132" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 132</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>